Done
Why can't we have multiple dumps running in parallel? Why do only user dumps have this restriction?

This issue was debated during our design meetings. We encountered a problem with the BMC when multiple dumps were initiated concurrently, leading us to decide to permit only one at a time. If multiple clients requested the same data, they would both be provided identical sets.

However, if multiple clients require the dump, each client must make an individual request. This is because the dump is typically offloaded to the client that made the request, which also has the capability to delete the dump. We need to revisit this issue or consider making this a build-time policy. I can incorporate this change in a separate commit.
Special case code is always where the bugs show up, do we really need this?
If user provided no inputs it should be a user requested dump
And we are allowing only one user requested bmc dump at a time - debatable
